    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="662"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">853.015311/2</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Portuguese Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Alte</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 4, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I was very gratified to receive
                    your letter of March 30, 1922, and I beg to thank you most cordially for <pb
                        facs="0883" n="769" xml:id="pg_769"/> your kind intervention in the incident
                    occasioned by the hauling down on February 22 of the Portuguese flag flying over
                    the Vice Consulate at Providence, R. I.</p>
                <p>I would esteem it a great favour if you would be good enough to convey to His
                    Excellency the Governor of the State of Rhode Island the assurance that the
                    Portuguese Government and I myself personally deeply appreciated the high sense
                    of international courtesy that inspired his action in this matter.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alte</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
